From support case:

{quote}
As you no doubt know, it's both possible and useful to customise ConfluenceActionSupport.properties by copying it to, for eg, C:/Confluence/2.10.3/confluence/WEB-INF/classes/com/atlassian/confluence/core then editing it.

But... if a string isn't found in there, Confluence doesn't use the value that is still in the jar.

It would make upgrading easier if it did, because it would provide back-compatibility - use the customisations if they exist, else use the current default. As is, a new upgrade means merging the files.
{quote}

