The {{\{recently-updated\}}} macro documentation states that you can include multiple spaces and negate spaces from selection:
From http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Recently+Updated+Macro#RecentlyUpdatedMacro-OptionalParameters:
{quote}
You can specify one or more space keys, separated by a comma or a space. 
To exclude content in a specific space, put a minus sign (-) immediately in front of that space key. For example: If you specify a space key of -BADSPACE you will get only content which is not in the BADSPACE.
{quote}
However, with the following markup:
{noformat}
h5.This should show nothing 
{recently-updated:spaces=-@all} 

h5.This should show everything except my own personal space 
{recently-updated:spaces=@all,-~pdzwart}
{noformat}
You do not end up with what you expect:
!http://img.skitch.com/20090519-dnird57d3geih6s4m4gqben8uj.jpg!

Proof of concept: https://qa-cac.atlassian.com/display/~pdzwart/Recently+updated+space+negation

