Apparently the chart macro accepts case insensitive parameter values which the macro browser doesn't currently support. It would be nice if the parameter definition included this information.

Original description:
Use the markup provided at http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Chart+Macro#ChartMacro-XYLineChart

{noformat}{chart:type=xyline}
||      || 12 || 14 || 23 ||
| Revenue | 41.1 | 31.8 | 12.4 |
| Expense | 31.1 | 41.8 | 43.6 |
{chart}
{noformat}

Edit this with the macro browser.

Because the parameter 'type=xyline' is not recognised as matching 'type=xyLine' the Macro Browser will incorrectly change this to a pie chart.

Macro Browser parameters should not be case sensitive.

