Filling this for a customer:

{quote}
It is critical for our IT support model that Wiki space administrators be able to import content [via Import Page from Disk or some other mechanism].  Our wiki administrators simply do not have the time to perform all the wiki migrations that are being planned, so the legacy wiki users must be able to use the UWC tool to export content to disk from thier old wiki, and then as a Confluence space administrator, be able to import that content into thier own wiki space.  Confluence is currently THE wiki solution for HP Software R&D and we have deployed a 3-node commerical cluster initially with potential plans to expand the number of nodes later as need requires.  The basic problem is that there is not going to be some full-time wiki/site administrator to help the users with migrating content to the new wiki. If the space administrator can upload the pages into the wiki space, that is exactly the sort of self-service functionality that we need. Anybody who is a site administrator is really not going to have time to do anything other than create the space, assign the space administrators to the space, or add users to groups. Not having the import functionality for the space administrator is a major issue for us.
{quote}

